PLAGUE - UGANDA
***************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
<http://www.fas.org/promed/ahead>
See Also
Plague, bubonic - Mozambique (02) 980218225625
Plague - Mozambique (Tete, Zambesia) 980929153005
Plague epidemiology (03) 980526221852
Plague facts 980805234800
Date: Sat, 07 Nov 1998 08:24:46 -0800
Source: WHO Outbreak page, 7 Nov 1998
Via: Dr. James Chin, CDPC-mail <jchin@cdpc.com>

The Ministry of Health of Uganda is investigating reports of plague in the
district of Arua. Since April, 49 cases have been reported. WHO is awaiting
confirmation of the number of deaths. Cases of human plague [presumably in
Uganda - ES have been recorded on 3 occasions over the past 30 years : in
1982 (153 cases, 3 deaths); 1986 (340 cases, 27 deaths); and 1993 (167
cases, 18 deaths).
